restore modules after test_no_astropy_import

This test checks if astropy modules are imported
during integration by removing some astropy
modules from sys.modules. Prior to this commit
the test did not restore the modules. Depending
on the order of tests this can create issues when
some astropy submodules are re-imported.

For example, since astropy.units is unloaded
by astropy.constants (which contains some Quantity
instances) the test will unload astropy.units
undefining Quantity. The constants will then
fail isinstance checks when astropy.units is
re-imported (as the new Quantity is not the same
as the old Quantity) resulting in issues
defining some units (like 'au').
